        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:57PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Hendersonville, or 4 miles west of Bat Cave,
moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fletcher, Bat Cave, Gerton, and Edneyville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
